            <p class="lead">Here's something most Ontario investors don't realize: <strong>Niagara Falls is one of the few cities where you can legally Airbnb an investment property</strong>. No principal residence requirement for their Vacation Rental Unit license. With 12+ million tourists visiting annually, that's a significant opportunity.</p>
            <p class="lead">But the rules are different from Toronto or Mississauga. There are two license types, a three-strike complaint system, and some unique requirements. Let me walk you through how it actually works.</p>
