                <path d="M12 8h.01"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="callout-content">
              <strong>The bachelor party problem:</strong> Niagara Falls sees a lot of bachelor/bachelorette groups. Three noise complaints from one wild weekend could cost you your license for six months. Many successful hosts use strict guest screening and house rules to avoid this.
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>After a Suspension</h3>
          <p>Once suspended, you cannot operate for 6 months. After that period, you can reapply, but the city considers your history. Repeated suspensions can lead to permanent license denial.</p>

          <h2 id="penalties">Fines and Penalties</h2>
          <p>Operating without a license or violating the bylaw comes with significant fines:</p>

          <div class="penalty-table">
            <div class="penalty-row">
              <span class="penalty-type">First offense</span>
              <span class="penalty-amount">Up to $50,000</span>
            </div>
            <div class="penalty-row">
